This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it introduces a new architecture for neural networks that incorporates external memory resources. It is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it discusses the training of the neural network using gradient descent. Additionally, it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category as it involves the development of a system that can perform tasks that require algorithmic reasoning. The paper also mentions the use of attentional processes, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper's preliminary results involve tasks related to sorting and recall, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
